ProcessDescription.ows:Title: Spatial analog of a target climate.
ProcessDescription.ows:Abstract: Spatial analogs based on the comparison of climate indices. The algorithm compares the distribution of the target indices with the distribution of spatially distributed candidate indices and returns a value measuring the dissimilarity between both distributions over the candidate grid.

Input.ows:Title: Candidate netCDF dataset
Input.ows:Abstract: NetCDF files or archive (tar/zip) storing the candidate indices. The output will be stored on this grid.

Input.ows:Title: Target netCDF dataset
Input.ows:Abstract: NetCDF files or archive (tar/zip).containing netcdf files storing the target indices.

Input.ows:Title: Target coordinates (lon,lat)
Input.ows:Abstract: Geographical coordinates (lon,lat) of the target location.

Input.ows:Title: Indices
Input.ows:Abstract: One or more climate indices to use for the comparison.

Input.ows:Title: Distance
Input.ows:Abstract: Dissimilarity metric comparing distributions.

Input.ows:Title: Candidate start date
Input.ows:Abstract: Beginning of period (YYYY-MM-DD) for candidate data. Defaults to first entry.

Input.ows:Title: Candidate end date
Input.ows:Abstract: End of period (YYYY-MM_DD) for candidate data. Defaults to last entry.

Input.ows:Title: Target start date
Input.ows:Abstract: Beginning of period (YYYY-MM-DD) for target data. Defaults to first entry.

Input.ows:Title: Target end date
Input.ows:Abstract: End of period (YYYY-MM_DD) for target data. Defaults to last entry.

Output.ows:Title: Dissimilarity values
Output.ows:Abstract: Dissimilarity between target at selected location and candidate distributions over the entire grid.

Output.ows:Title: Logging information
Output.ows:Abstract: Collected logs during process run.

Input.ows:Abstract: Choose Earth Observation Products

Input.ows:Title: Bounding Box
Input.ows:Abstract: Enter a bbox: min_lon, max_lon, min_lat, max_lat. min_lon=Western longitude, max_lon=Eastern longitude, min_lat=Southern or northern latitude, max_lat=Northern or southern latitude. For example: -80,50,20,70

Input.ows:Title: Start Date
Input.ows:Abstract: First day of the period to be searched for EO data.(if not set, 30 days befor end of period will be selected

Input.ows:Title: End Date
Input.ows:Abstract: Last day of the period to be searched for EO data.(if not set, current day is set.)

Input.ows:Title: Cloud Cover
Input.ows:Abstract: Max tollerated percentage of cloud cover

Input.ows:Title: User Name
Input.ows:Abstract: Authentification user name for the COPERNICUS Sci-hub

Input.ows:Title: Password
Input.ows:Abstract: Authentification password for the COPERNICUS Sci-hub

Output.ows:Title: Files search result
Output.ows:Abstract: Files found according to the search querry

Output.ows:Title: Extend of tiles
Output.ows:Abstract: Map showing the extends of the found EO data

Output.ows:Title: Logging information
Output.ows:Abstract: Collected logs during process run.

ProcessDescription.ows:Title: Number of freeze-thaw events
ProcessDescription.ows:Abstract: Number of freeze-thaw events, where freezing and thawing occurs once a threshold of degree days below or above 0C is reached. A complete cycle (freeze-thaw-freeze) will return a value of 2.

Input.ows:Title: Resource
Input.ows:Abstract: NetCDF Files or archive (tar/zip) containing netCDF files.

Input.ows:Title: Grouping
Input.ows:Abstract: Temporal group over which the index is computed.

Input.ows:Title: Threshold
Input.ows:Abstract: The number of degree-days above or below the freezing point after which theground is considered frozen or thawed.

Output.ows:Title: Function output in netCDF
Output.ows:Abstract: The indicator values computed on the original input grid.

Output.ows:Title: Logging information
Output.ows:Abstract: Collected logs during process run.

ProcessDescription.ows:Title: Duration
ProcessDescription.ows:Abstract: Summarizes consecutive occurrences in a sequence where the logical operation returns TRUE. The summary operation is applied to the sequences within a temporal aggregation.

Input.ows:Title: Resource
Input.ows:Abstract: NetCDF Files or archive (tar/zip) containing netCDF files.

Input.ows:Title: Grouping
Input.ows:Abstract: Temporal group over which the index is computed.

Input.ows:Title: Threshold
Input.ows:Abstract: The threshold value to use for the logical operation.

Input.ows:Title: Operation
Input.ows:Abstract: The logical operation. One of 'gt','gte','lt', or 'lte'.

Input.ows:Title: Summary
Input.ows:Abstract: The summary operation to apply the durations. One of 'mean','median','std','max', or 'min'.

Output.ows:Title: Function output in netCDF
Output.ows:Abstract: The indicator values computed on the original input grid.

Output.ows:Title: Logging information
Output.ows:Abstract: Collected logs during process run.
